tex-full-svg-a11y.min.js — vendored MathJax bundle (decision A)
================================================================

WHAT
  A single self-contained MathJax 4.1.2 "custom combined component": TeX input +
  SVG output + ALL 41 TeX extensions + the full a11y set (assistive-mml, sre,
  semantic-enrich, speech, explorer, complexity), all PRELOADED (no runtime lazy
  loading). SVG output embeds glyph path data, so no font files are fetched.

WHY THIS FORM
  The app must render math with NO CDN and fully offline, for both the live
  preview (asset-protocol URL) and the self-contained HTML export
  (`--mathjax=file://<this> --embed-resources`, which inlines it into one file).
  A single preloaded component is the only shape that is self-contained AND emits
  assistive MathML offline: loading a11y as a second <script> does not register
  it, and loading the bundle from a data: URL breaks MathJax's base-path
  detection. See .agents/memories/mathjax-offline-local-source-decision.md.

VERSION
  MathJax 4.1.2 (npm `@mathjax/src@4.1.2`). Size: 2004835 bytes.

REPRODUCIBLE BUILD
  mkdir -p /tmp/mjbuild && cd /tmp/mjbuild && npm init -y
  npm i @mathjax/src@4
  npm i -D webpack@^5 webpack-cli@^7 terser-webpack-plugin@^5
  cd node_modules/@mathjax/src/components/mjs
  mkdir tex-full-svg-a11y
  cat > tex-full-svg-a11y/config.json <<'EOF'
  { "webpack": { "name": "tex-full-svg-a11y", "dist": "." } }
  EOF
  # tex-full-svg-a11y/tex-full-svg-a11y.js imports: startup/init, loader,
  #   core, input/tex + EVERY input/tex/extensions/<name>/<name>.js (all 41),
  #   output/svg (loadFont(startup,true)), ui/menu, a11y/util,
  #   a11y/assistive-mml, a11y/complexity, input/mml; then
  #   Loader.preLoaded(...all of the above incl 'a11y/sre','a11y/semantic-enrich',
  #   'a11y/speech','a11y/explorer' and every '[tex]/<name>'); and sets
  #   MathJax.config.tex.packages = [...all 41 names...].
  node ../bin/makeAll --mjs --no-subdirs tex-full-svg-a11y
  # output: tex-full-svg-a11y/tex-full-svg-a11y.min.js  (== this file)

VERIFIED (offline, chromium setOffline(true) + route-abort of non-file/data/blob)
  - `\(\zeta(2)=\pi^2/6\)` -> 1 mjx-container, no merror,
    assistive MathML "ζ⁡(2)=π2/6" (U+2061 normalized -> "ζ(2)=π2/6").
  - 0 remote requests. Multi-extension (color, bbox, cancel, mhchem) also clean.
  - pandoc inlines it: `pandoc in.md -s --mathjax=file://<this> --embed-resources -o out.html`.

KNOWN LIMITATION (follow-up, non-blocking)
  The SRE speech/explorer path eagerly tries to spawn a Web Worker from
  `file:///sre/speech-worker.js`, which 404s. It logs ONE harmless pageerror and
  does NOT block rendering, assistive MathML, or cause any remote request.
  Interactive spoken-math/exploration therefore needs a follow-up (ship sre/ as a
  co-located resource for the preview + configure the worker path; single-file
  export cannot host a worker). Static accessibility (assistive MathML) works now.
